wfTokenRingEntry.name: wfTokenRingEntry
wfTokenRingEntry.description: An entry in the token table

wfTokenRingState.name: wfTokenRingState
wfTokenRingState.description: line driver state variable, Not Present, Init, Down, Up

wfTokenRingSlot.name: wfTokenRingSlot
wfTokenRingSlot.description: instance ID Slot, filled in by driver

wfTokenRingConnector.name: wfTokenRingConnector
wfTokenRingConnector.description: instance ID Connector, filled in by driver. For the ASN this attribute is an encoded value and is equal to 'module'*10 + 'connector'. Where 'module' is defined in attribute 70 and 'connector' is defined in attribute 71 of this table. For non-ASN platforms this attribute is the phisical connector number on the slot

wfTokenRingCct.name: wfTokenRingCct
wfTokenRingCct.description: cct number for this line instance, configuration required

wfTokenRingMtu.name: wfTokenRingMtu
wfTokenRingMtu.description: mtu parameter, fixed. This mtu of 4568 allows a type 3 Source Route Frame (info=4472) to be IP encapsulated over Token Ring. The components are: AC_FC (2) + SNAP (12+8) + SNAP_IP (12+8+20) + SR (12+18) + TYPE3_INFO (4472) + FCS (4) --------------------- total 4568 bytes

wfTokenRingMadr.name: wfTokenRingMadr
wfTokenRingMadr.description: line MAC address, line driver fills in the currently used 48 bit MAC address.

wfTokenRingCfgMadr.name: wfTokenRingCfgMadr
wfTokenRingCfgMadr.description: Configured line MAC address. Only used if wfTokenRingMadrSelect is set appropriately.

wfTokenRingMadrSelect.name: wfTokenRingMadrSelect
wfTokenRingMadrSelect.description: Selector determines which MAC address the interface will use.

wfTokenRingSpeed.name: wfTokenRingSpeed
wfTokenRingSpeed.description: Token Ring speed parameter - 4 and 16 Mbps are only valid values

wfTokenRingEarlyTokenRelease.name: wfTokenRingEarlyTokenRelease
wfTokenRingEarlyTokenRelease.description: Early Token Release parameter, only valid with 16Mbps

wfTokenRingStatus.name: wfTokenRingStatus
wfTokenRingStatus.description: The current interface status. This attribute is only valid when the wfTokenRingOpenState attribute is set to OPENED. The attribute's value is a sum of values, one for each currently applicable condition (ie, bit positions indicate active conditions). Occurrences of each condition are separately counted and the counts are included in this MIB as attributes wfTokenRingSignalLosses through wfTokenRingRingRecoveries. The following values are defined: 32768 = Signal Losses 16384 = Hard Errors 8192 = Soft Errors 4096 = Transmit Beacons 2048 = Lobe Wire Faults 1024 = Auto-Removal Errors 256 = Remove Received 128 = Counter Overflows 64 = Single Stations 32 = Ring Recoveries This attribute is the most recent sum of these conditions. More information on each condition is include in the descriptions of the individual counter attributes.

wfTokenRingOpenState.name: wfTokenRingOpenState
wfTokenRingOpenState.description: The current interface state with respect to entering or leaving the ring.

wfTokenRingOpenStatus.name: wfTokenRingOpenStatus
wfTokenRingOpenStatus.description: Indicates the success, or the reason for failure, of the station's most recent attempt to enter the ring.

wfTokenRingUpStream.name: wfTokenRingUpStream
wfTokenRingUpStream.description: MAC address of Up Stream neighbor. Only valid when 'opened'.

wfTokenRingRxOctets.name: wfTokenRingRxOctets
wfTokenRingRxOctets.description: Number of octets received without error.

wfTokenRingRxFrames.name: wfTokenRingRxFrames
wfTokenRingRxFrames.description: Number of frames received without error.

wfTokenRingTxOctets.name: wfTokenRingTxOctets
wfTokenRingTxOctets.description: Number of octets transmitted without error.

wfTokenRingTxFrames.name: wfTokenRingTxFrames
wfTokenRingTxFrames.description: Number of frames transmitted without error.

wfTokenRingInDiscards.name: wfTokenRingInDiscards
wfTokenRingInDiscards.description: Number of error-free inbound packets discarded. Usually due to lack of memory resources. This is equivalent to wfTokenRingRxCongestionErrors.

wfTokenRingInErrors.name: wfTokenRingInErrors
wfTokenRingInErrors.description: Number of inbound packets not delivered to higher-layer protocol due to errors. The sum of wfTokenRingLineErrors and wfTokenRingBurstErrors.

wfTokenRingOutDiscards.name: wfTokenRingOutDiscards
wfTokenRingOutDiscards.description: Number of error-free outbound packets discarded. Usually due to lack of transmission bandwidth. This is equivalent to wfTokenRingTxClipFrames.

wfTokenRingOutErrors.name: wfTokenRingOutErrors
wfTokenRingOutErrors.description: Number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors. This is equivalent to wfTokenRingLostFrameErrors.

wfTokenRingTxClipFrames.name: wfTokenRingTxClipFrames
wfTokenRingTxClipFrames.description: Number of frames clipped in driver's transmit routine due to transmit congestion.

wfTokenRingRxReplenMisses.name: wfTokenRingRxReplenMisses
wfTokenRingRxReplenMisses.description: Number of packet buffer misses while attempting to replenish driver receive ring.

wfTokenRingSignalLosses.name: wfTokenRingSignalLosses
wfTokenRingSignalLosses.description: Number of ring signal losses detected.

wfTokenRingHardErrors.name: wfTokenRingHardErrors
wfTokenRingHardErrors.description: Number of events causing the adapter to transmit or receive beacon MAC frames.

wfTokenRingSoftErrors.name: wfTokenRingSoftErrors
wfTokenRingSoftErrors.description: Number of soft errors. Corresponds to the number of Report Error MAC frames transmitted by this station.

wfTokenRingTransmitBeacons.name: wfTokenRingTransmitBeacons
wfTokenRingTransmitBeacons.description: Number of events causing the adapter to transmit beacon frames.

wfTokenRingLobeWireFaults.name: wfTokenRingLobeWireFaults
wfTokenRingLobeWireFaults.description: Number of opens or shorts (cable faults) between the adapter and the MAU.

wfTokenRingAutoRemovalErrors.name: wfTokenRingAutoRemovalErrors
wfTokenRingAutoRemovalErrors.description: Number of lobe wrap test failures during beacon auto_removal process.

wfTokenRingRequestRemoves.name: wfTokenRingRequestRemoves
wfTokenRingRequestRemoves.description: Number of Remove Ring Station MAC frames received. Each frame causes this station to leave the ring.

wfTokenRingCounterOverflows.name: wfTokenRingCounterOverflows
wfTokenRingCounterOverflows.description: Number of adapter error counter overflows.

wfTokenRingSingleStations.name: wfTokenRingSingleStations
wfTokenRingSingleStations.description: Number of ring status change interrupts while adapter is only station on the ring.

wfTokenRingRingRecoveries.name: wfTokenRingRingRecoveries
wfTokenRingRingRecoveries.description: Number of claim token MAC frames (ring recoveries) observed on the ring.

wfTokenRingAdapterChecks.name: wfTokenRingAdapterChecks
wfTokenRingAdapterChecks.description: Number of internal adapter errors that result in adapter crashes.

wfTokenRingFirstAdapterCheckCode.name: wfTokenRingFirstAdapterCheckCode
wfTokenRingFirstAdapterCheckCode.description: Adapter Check Code of first occurrence.

wfTokenRingLastAdapterCheckCode.name: wfTokenRingLastAdapterCheckCode
wfTokenRingLastAdapterCheckCode.description: Adapter Check Code of most recent (last) occurrence.

wfTokenRingLineErrors.name: wfTokenRingLineErrors
wfTokenRingLineErrors.description: Number of frames copied or repeated by this station with bad format or an FCS error.

wfTokenRingBurstErrors.name: wfTokenRingBurstErrors
wfTokenRingBurstErrors.description: Number of errored frames with no transition for 5 1/2 bit times.

wfTokenRingAriFciErrors.name: wfTokenRingAriFciErrors
wfTokenRingAriFciErrors.description: Number of occurrences of this station receiving both an AMP MAC frame and a SMP MAC frame with the a & c bits clear or more than one SMP MAC frame with the a & c bits clear without an intervening AMP MAC frame. This condition indicates that the up-stream neighbor is unable to set the a & c bits in a frame that it has copied.

wfTokenRingLostFrameErrors.name: wfTokenRingLostFrameErrors
wfTokenRingLostFrameErrors.description: Number of frames being stripped which are missing their tails.

wfTokenRingRxCongestionErrors.name: wfTokenRingRxCongestionErrors
wfTokenRingRxCongestionErrors.description: Number of frames dropped due to receive congestion.

wfTokenRingFrameCopiedErrors.name: wfTokenRingFrameCopiedErrors
wfTokenRingFrameCopiedErrors.description: Number of specifically addressed frames for this station that had their a & c bits previously set.

wfTokenRingTokenErrors.name: wfTokenRingTokenErrors
wfTokenRingTokenErrors.description: Number of token protocol errors. Only relevant when this station is the active monitor.

wfTokenRingDmaBusErrors.name: wfTokenRingDmaBusErrors
wfTokenRingDmaBusErrors.description: Number of bus errors during DMA that do not exceed threshold.

wfTokenRingDmaParityErrors.name: wfTokenRingDmaParityErrors
wfTokenRingDmaParityErrors.description: Number of parity errors during DMA that do not exceed threshold.

wfTokenRingSrbNotFreeCmdAborts.name: wfTokenRingSrbNotFreeCmdAborts
wfTokenRingSrbNotFreeCmdAborts.description: Number of host to adapter commands aborted because of in-completed in process commands.

wfTokenRingRxProcessings.name: wfTokenRingRxProcessings
wfTokenRingRxProcessings.description: Number of processings of received frames (similar to RINT).

wfTokenRingTxProcessings.name: wfTokenRingTxProcessings
wfTokenRingTxProcessings.description: Number of processings of frames for transmit.

wfTokenRingTxCmplProcessings.name: wfTokenRingTxCmplProcessings
wfTokenRingTxCmplProcessings.description: Number of processings of transmitted frames (similar to TINT).

wfTokenRingRxTimeouts.name: wfTokenRingRxTimeouts
wfTokenRingRxTimeouts.description: Number of re-initializations due to receiver time-outs.

wfTokenRingCmdTimeouts.name: wfTokenRingCmdTimeouts
wfTokenRingCmdTimeouts.description: Number of re-initializations due to command time-outs.

wfTokenRingRxHostIntErrors.name: wfTokenRingRxHostIntErrors
wfTokenRingRxHostIntErrors.description: Number of re-initializations due to receive host interface errors.

wfTokenRingCfgTxQueueLength.name: wfTokenRingCfgTxQueueLength
wfTokenRingCfgTxQueueLength.description: Configured Transmit Queue Length. Values other than zero over-ride the router selected values. A value of zero has a special meaning. Zero causes router based default values to be used. Values larger than the compiled ring size are truncated to the compiled ring size.

wfTokenRingCfgRxQueueLength.name: wfTokenRingCfgRxQueueLength
wfTokenRingCfgRxQueueLength.description: Configured Receive Queue Length. Values other than zero over-ride the router selected values. A value of zero has a special meaning. Zero causes router based default values to be used. Values larger than the compiled ring size are truncated to the compiled ring size.

wfTokenRingMacRxOctets.name: wfTokenRingMacRxOctets
wfTokenRingMacRxOctets.description: Number of Mac frame octets received without error.

wfTokenRingMacRxFrames.name: wfTokenRingMacRxFrames
wfTokenRingMacRxFrames.description: Number of Mac frames received without error.

wfTokenRingCfgFunctionalAddress.name: wfTokenRingCfgFunctionalAddress
wfTokenRingCfgFunctionalAddress.description: The configurable bit mask of all Token Ring Functional addresses for which this interface will accept frames. This value is loaded into the func addr defined in the attribute 'wfTokenRingFunctionalAddress.' note: 2147467520 = 0x7fffc100

wfTokenRingFunctionalAddress.name: wfTokenRingFunctionalAddress
wfTokenRingFunctionalAddress.description: The bit mask of all Token Ring Functional addresses for which this interface will accept frames.

wfTokenRingGroupAddress.name: wfTokenRingGroupAddress
wfTokenRingGroupAddress.description: The single Token Ring Group address for which this interface will accept frames.

wfTokenRingLineNumber.name: wfTokenRingLineNumber
wfTokenRingLineNumber.description: Logical line number associated with this driver entity.

wfTokenRingMacCode.name: wfTokenRingMacCode
wfTokenRingMacCode.description: Type and version of microcode running on the TMS380.

wfTokenRingModule.name: wfTokenRingModule
wfTokenRingModule.description: Module number for ASN platform, filled in by driver. For non-ASN platforms this attribute will not be used.

wfTokenRingActualConnector.name: wfTokenRingActualConnector
wfTokenRingActualConnector.description: Actual connector number for ASN platform, filled in by driver. For non-ASN platforms this attribute will not be used.

wfTokenRingLastChange.name: wfTokenRingLastChange
wfTokenRingLastChange.description: The value of SysUpTime at the time the interface entered it's current operational state (UP state). SysUpTime is defined as the time (in hundredths of a second) since the network management portion of the system was last re-initialized. Usually the time since boot.

wfTokenRingOutQLen.name: wfTokenRingOutQLen
wfTokenRingOutQLen.description: The instantaneous current length of the output packet queue (in packets).

wfTokenRingForceMacCode.name: wfTokenRingForceMacCode
wfTokenRingForceMacCode.description: Selector determines which microcode will be downloaded for the TMS380.

wfTokenRingMSBMadr.name: wfTokenRingMSBMadr
wfTokenRingMSBMadr.description: Provides this interface's MAC address in Most Significant Bit (MSB) format. This format is also referred to as Token Ring or IBM format. This MAC address is the same MAC address as given in the wfTokenRingMadr attribute except that wfTokenRingMadr is displayed in ethernet format.

wfTokenRingTurboBoflDebug.name: wfTokenRingTurboBoflDebug
wfTokenRingTurboBoflDebug.description: Special Turbo-BOFL debug mechanism to be used by Engineering and Manufacturing only. 31-24 : TMO - period of breath (amount of time between successive breaths of life) 23-16 : Number of packets per breath. 15-0 : Packet length in bytes - 22 bytes minimum. All bits set to zero will disable this attribute.
